  "summary": "Anthony Ked, a quick-witted tour guide for the Jazzy High-End Tour Group, meets an old friend, Jimmy McGregor, while managing a group of tourists in Bravaio. The group, consisting of seven women and three men, is currently bored and waiting for a drive to Matopos. During their brief interaction, Jimmy remarks on Anthony's tendency to find trouble and his perceived lack of fear regarding death. Anthony later manages the group's needs, which include consoling an irate gentleman, assisting an elderly woman with postcards, and flirting with Miss Taylor, a young and frivolous tourist. While leading the group to a café, Anthony tells Miss Taylor about their first meeting in Africa seven years prior, claiming they rescued Jimmy from being eaten by a tribe.\n\nThat evening, Anthony visits Jimmy in his room. Anthony expresses dissatisfaction with his current job and asks Jimmy for employment opportunities. Jimmy offers Anthony a job located in Britain, though he explains he is declining it because he intends to travel to the interior of the country to mine for gold. Jimmy mentions a connection to Heslovsky, prompting Anthony to describe his knowledge of the Balkan Peninsula nation. Anthony notes that Heslovsky is a place of frequent riots and revolutions, following the assassination of King Nicholas IV seven years ago, which transformed the country into a republic.",
